cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with unsupervised deep learning methods applied to sets of notions of different levels and measures, in order to establish a unified vector representation of the outer world by combining notions of different kinds into a unique conceptual framework. This involves the use of graph and word embedding-like techniques, which are commonly used in natural language processing and computer vision, suggesting that the paper could be categorized under cs.CL, cs.CV, or cs.AI. Additionally, the paper deals with the alignment of two embedding spaces in a purely unsupervised way, which is a common problem in machine learning and could be categorized under cs.LG or cs.NE. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, and cs.NE, in that order.
